09/07/2003
RUSE, Bulgaria -- Meeting Tuesday (8 July), members of a Bulgarian-Romanian expert commission announced that their countries are preparing a long-term project, financed with 360m euros from the European Commission, to upgrade the Danube waterway. The project, to be completed by 2007, would facilitate water traffic in the common section of the river between the islands of Belene and Batin. A Dutch company has been hired to prepare a feasibility study. (BTA, News.bg - 08/07/03)
